<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-07-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="520" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d520">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Russell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States to Venezuela</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">San Juan, P. R.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-07-31"><hi rend="italic">July
                                        31, 1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Russell reports that a revolutionary force from Colombia, commanded
                            by an important Venezuelan, Rangel Garbiras, is invading Venezuela,
                            which Government has sent 10,000 men to meet the invading force, and
                            that all individual guaranties under the constitution have been
                            suspended by the President of Venezuela.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>